  "tier": "transcendental",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Voice 1 in notch filter mode, Voice 2 in bandpass. Same cutoff frequencies but opposite filter behaviors — what Voice 1 removes, Voice 2 emphasizes. HAMMER at 0.0 (neutral) so the two filtering strategies coexist without interaction. LFO1 sweeps Voice 1's notch cutoff at 0.4 Hz (triangle); LFO2 sweeps Voice 2's bandpass cutoff at 0.63 Hz (coprime). The scanning never repeats. Both voices on Wavetable for complex source material.",
